The paper proposes a meta-learning framework for knowledge graph completion that focuses on handling infrequent relations and uncommon entities. This involves using textual descriptions to extract key information and a generative model to enhance performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.CL (computation and language) as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves developing a novel model, which falls under cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.IR (information retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which falls under cs.DB (databases).
